Reasoning: The paper deals with the diversity-multiplexing tradeoff (DMT) of cooperative networks using various relaying protocols. This topic falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of pulse amplitude modulation (PAM) signals and shaping waveforms also suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.MM). The study of the DMT performance of the system also involves analyzing the system's behavior under different conditions, which can be related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of relaying protocols and cooperative networks involves communication and networking (cs.COMM).
